<TITLE> 3 killed in road accidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 12 (bdnew24.com)Three persons including a sub-inspector of police were killed in three separate road accidents in Netrakona, Gazipur and Barisal. bdnews24.com correspondent from Netrakona reports that a sub-inspector of Kalmakanda Police Station was killed in a road accident on Friday night. The deceased, Manirul Islam, 46, was from Hidrankhali village of Karimganj Upazila in Kishoreganj. He joined the station a month ago. Islam, riding on a motorbike, was injured after a tempo in Baishdar area of Netrakona Sadar Upazila hit him from behind on Thursday afternoon. He was admitted to Mymensingh Medical College Hospital, where he died on Friday night. bdnews24.com Gazipur correspondent reports that an elderly woman crashed under a car at Sadar Upazila on Friday. Nawjor Highway Police Camp sergeant Mostafizur Rahman told bdnews24.com: "A private car ran over the woman in Maleker Bari area around 9pm on Friday." The deceased was identified as Charubala Das, 50, wife of Nagendra Das of Bamerchar village under Mohanganj Upazila in Netrakona. Following the incident, angry locals blocked Dhaka-Mymensingh highway for half an hour until police took control of the situation around 10pm. Due to requests from the relatives, her body was handed over without autopsy on that night, the police officer added. bdnews24.com Barisal correspondent reports that a bus ran over a motorbike-rider in Batajor area on Barisal-Dhaka highway on Saturday morning. The dead, identified as Md Firoz Mridha, 27, was the son of Abdul Mannan of Basudevpur village of Gournadi Upazila. Gournadi police chief Md Mozammel Haque said that the accident took place when a Dhaka-bound bus and a rented motorbike collided head-on near Batajor Ashwini Kumar High School around 11am. Firoz died in Gournadi Health Complex, where he was admitted with serious injuries. Police arrested bus driver Anishur Rahman, 40, and seized the bus too. The body was sent to Barisal Medical College Hospital for autopsy. Firoz's family was taking preparation to file a case in this concern, the police officer added. bdnews24.com
